==English==
===Etymology===
{{ME.}} enemite, from {{OF.}} enemistie, from Vulgar {{L.}} inimicitia, from {{L.}} inimicus ''[[enemy]]''

===Noun===
'''enmity''' (plural ''enmities'')

# a deep-seated [[hatred]] or [[animosity]], often [[mutual]]
# the emotion of a person or people who are hostile, "Chris and Jamie could no longer contain their enmity"

compare, [[enemy]] (a foe)

===Synonyms===
* [[hostility]], [[antagonism]], [[animosity]], [[rancor]], [[antipathy]], [[animus]]

